                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Moore</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Herdliska</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On receiving Saturday report from consul at Geneva, the President telegraphed to
                    the Emperor extending sincere condolences. His Majesty has replied. You will
                    advise Mr. Tower, so that he can return to attend obsequies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
